Purpose
=======

A prospective business owner in the Chicago Metro Area has
many locations to choose for locating a new storefront.
Contributing considerations include

- Zoning
- Tax or other incentives
- Type of existing businesses
- Likelihood for success
    + Historical success of similar businesses
    + Local socioeconomic environment
    + Nearby transportation


Data
====

Main resources
--------------

- Census: [Chicago socioeconomic census data](https://data.cityofchicago.org/Health-Human-Services/Census-Data-Selected-socioeconomic-indicators-in-C/kn9c-c2s2)
- Zoning
    + Boundaries: [Chicago zoning boundaries](https://data.cityofchicago.org/Community-Economic-Development/Boundaries-Zoning-Districts/ys52-bf79)
    + Businesses: [Chicago zoning business table](http://www.cityofchicago.org/content/dam/city/depts/bacp/pictures/businessusetable110410.pdf)
    + Ordinance: [Chicago zoning ordinance](http://www.amlegal.com/nxt/gateway.dll/Illinois/chicagozoning/chicagozoningordinanceandlanduseordinanc?f=templates$fn=default.htm$3.0$vid=amlegal:chicagozoning_il)
- Business licenses: [Current and historical business licenses](https://data.cityofchicago.org/Community-Economic-Development/Business-Licenses/r5kz-chrr)
- NAICS: [NAICS Descriptions](http://www.census.gov/econ/cbp/download/NAICS2012.txt)
- Trends: [Census County Business Patterns](https://www.census.gov/econ/cbp/download)


Possible other resources
------------------------

- Broadband: [Broadband innovation zones](https://data.cityofchicago.org/Community-Economic-Development/Broadband-Innovation-Zones/jkfs-hwcr)
- Community: [Community enterprise zones](https://data.cityofchicago.org/Community-Economic-Development/Boundaries-Enterprise-Zones/64xf-pyvh)
- TIF: [Tax Increment Financing districts](https://data.cityofchicago.org/Community-Economic-Development/Boundaries-Tax-Increment-Financing-Districts/iyec-2es5)
- Planning: [Planning Districts](https://data.cityofchicago.org/Community-Economic-Development/Boundaries-Planning-Districts/5xt8-wz7f)
- Empowerment: [Empowerment Zones](https://data.cityofchicago.org/Community-Economic-Development/Boundaries-Empowerment-Zones/m6ef-sjkj)


DesiredUI
=========

1. User selects a NAICS category from a dropdown and the permissible zones highlight
2. User hovers over a highlighted zone and
    a. 3 Nearest EL stops light
    b. 3 Nearest Divvy stops light
    c. Likelihood that the business will be open in a certain
       number of years based on a regression on similar business's
       longevity and the local socioeconomic environment
           i. 1 year
           ii. 2 years
           iii. 5 years
    d. A chart with the most relevant (highest P-value) socioeconomic
       factors, year over year
    e. A chart with the most relevant (similar NAICS) businesses
       count year over year


Roadmap
=======

1. Merge the datasets
2. Render the zones on the webpage
3. Connect the dataset to the webpage (REST to HDFS)
